Marble #49 || 45mm
The big victory on this marble was preserving the clarity of that 12mm pinfire RGB opal. Black base opals don't tolerate heat or stress well at all, and to be honest I usually mess them up. They're also rather expensive at this size, so needless to say I'm thrilled that the risk paid off. One of the s3xiest st0nes I've seen in a while 💎💎 
The awection for this marble starts today in my private group chat, at 12pm noon MST. 📥 #glassart #marble #glassblowing #handmade #headyart #headyglass #marblesofig #mib #bestofglass

Marble #50 ~ 43mm

I knew I wanted to make something special for number 50. I tried going big with size, I tried implementing some new techs. But ultimately, the best thing I can do to continue upgrading my work is to focus on color and composition.  Those have always been the most important components of dotstacking in my eyes.

The awection for this marble will start tomorrow in my private group chat - just DM to join if you haven't already. Thank you 🙏🙏#dotstack #marble #pooleyglass #bestofglass #headyart #headyglass #marblesofig

[sold out] Helloooo there! Long time no postie... I have been up to several large projects this month, and I just don't love any of them so it's hard to get excited about sharing those pieces. That said, I will be offering several large marbles on my story today, for the loww. 
As a way of clearing my head I decided I should scale down and make a small batch of slurper-sized "glass eyes" with pretty colors and fancy implosions. 

🟢Green/grey: Hydra (cfl) | 23mm | 💲325
🔵Blue: Blue Dream | 25mm | 💲300
🟡Yellow: Pineapple Juice | 25mm | 💲200 (2nd quality)

I really enjoyed making these, let me know what you guys think! Should I make more marbles in this price range, or continue to shoot for the stars? 

#glassmarbles #bestofglass #glasseye #marblesofig #pooleyglass #glassblowing #glassart #headyglass

Marble #58 || 36mm

I found it very difficult to capture the vibrancy and shift of "Mischief," the badass CFL color from @northstarglass with which I created this orb. 

It's been a while since I've released something and I'm hoping I can get a decent turnout for this awection. I'll host it in my private group chat w no BIN, starting today at 12pm MST and running for 48hrs. 

If you have any questions please feel free to leave a comment or DM and I will clear things up for you. 

As always I would greatly appreciate anyone who takes the time to show this post some love! Instagram is an increasingly difficult place for small businesses to gain exposure, but I am determined as ever to create beautiful glass and share it with enthusiasts! Thank you ❤️🙏

I have a large body of work prepared for Marble Masters 6, and I'm quite proud of it. If you're at the show tomorrow, be sure to stop by my table and see what I've been working so hard for. Building enough inventory for a show meant taking about 2 months off from internet sales, so I'm really hoping it pays off! 

Chasing a dream as an artist often means taking risks and doing things that scare you. Showing up to a swanky gallery in LA with my case of orbs, rubbing shoulders with successful artists; these are frightening prospects for a small-town glass crafter like myself. 

But the hard work is over, and now I just have to show up.
Thank you to @marblemasters6 @danceswithnugrun for the amazing opportunity. I truly cannot wait.

#bestofglass #marblemasters #marblesofig #glassofig #headyglass #glassart #handmade #glassblowing #artist

Marbles #56 and #60 sold to @dustin_bowls_ at Marble Masters 6. #56 is the largest I've ever made and #60 is definitely one of my all-time favorites. I forgot to photograph the majority of what I sold at MM6 but these are definitely some highlights. Thanks to everyone who showed their face at my booth, it was a real pleasure to meet collectors and artists alike.

Marble #71 || 31mm 
The order in which I release my next 6 or so marbles will be kinda random. They are the unsold pieces I prepared for MM6 and I want to start with one i know I haven't shared here. The CFL color "Gemini" has a lot of color variation depending on the light source. From violet, to magenta, to almost clear. 
This marble will go up for auction in my private group chat, simply click the link in my bio if you'd like to join! Hint: orbs in this size range are more affordable!

Marble #74 || 33mm
I've used a lot of opals during my time as a lampworker, few as stunning as this tumbled slab from @grandpaglass. Overall I'm thrilled with the cleanliness and aesthetic of this marble. I can always point out something wrong with my work, but this is a rare example of a piece I consider nearly flawless. 
The video sequence goes from CFL light to LED light in order to show the color shift from "silver potion." (Ik, it looks like serum). This marble is going up in my private au*tion group today at 12pm MST. Link in bio or DM me to join 🙏🙏 #pooleyglass #bestofglass #marble #marblesofig #headyglass #headyart #glassofig

This was a fun one! Join my aucti*n group if you're interested in acquiring it. I plan to run this session a little differently; This evening I will open up only 4 HOURS for bidding, so don't miss out!

Marble #65 || 47mm 
I hope everyone had a fantastic holiday this year. I have a few 2023 marbles left to sell, but we'll just let this one cap off the year. This marble will go up for a 4 hour awection tomorrow (Sunday) in my private group chat. Click the link in my bio to join, or dm me if you have trouble. Thank you for looking 🙏 In light of everything that's gone haywire this year, in both the world and the glass industry, I am so grateful to have people supporting my work and enabling me to continue this creative journey. 🐒
